Largest specimen reported in literature: 460 mm TL (
Carneiro & Castro, 2005
).

Conservation: At first glance, the fish fauna of the western Atlantic is relatively homogeneous, although a growing number of recent studies indicate that the southwestern Atlantic is home to a substantial number of endemic species. Over the past years several new species were described or revalidated, while at least another 40 species have been identified as unknown and are being described (e.g.
Figueiredo et al. , 2002
;
Rocha, 2004
;
Bernardes et al. , 2005
;
Melo, 2007
;
Floeter et al. , 2008
;
Mincarone & Anderson, 2008
;
Sazima et al., 2008
; Carvalho-Filho & Floeter, in preparation).
